- Reasoning: The Voyage-4 1024d premise is obsolete. Current default is local 768d: persisted/healthy Ollama `nomic-embed-text-v1.5`, otherwise hf-local `nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5`; Voyage is `voyage-code-3` 1024d only when explicitly selected or reached by last-resort fallback. Because cache rows are scoped by profile/provider/dim/input kind, a Voyage cache cannot be assumed populated or reusable for Ollama/hf-local trigger matching.
- Recommended action: Rescope 007 before implementation. Replace all hardcoded Voyage/Voyage-4/1024 assumptions with active `EmbeddingProfile`/`profile_key` handling, retune thresholds/goldens for 768d Nomic, update stale paths to current `handlers/save/embedding-pipeline.ts`, and decide whether prompt embeddings use query-cache-only lookup or bounded local generation. Keep 008/002 as feedback-weight rerank, but drop any older hidden references to model/Voyage reranking.
